definition.message:
Memory pressure (`full` avg10) is above 10% on {{host.name}}. The system is spending significant time with EVERY task stalled on memory, which usually means swap thrashing or imminent OOM kills.

Investigate immediately: check `free -m`, `vmstat`, and the OOM killer log (`dmesg | grep -i killed`). Consider adding memory, reducing the working set, or enabling memory cgroup limits to localize the problem.

@pagerduty
@all
